entries.title: UNESCO Designates Odesa a World Heritage Site Amid Russian Attacks
entries.description: The Black Sea port has been battered by Russian shelling for months.

entries.title: U.N. Official Fired in Investment Scandal
entries.description: A second top United Nations official is out of a job following the disclosure that more than $20 million doled out in unconventional loans may be lost.

entries.title: Newly Discovered Asteroid to Pass Close to Earth Tonight
entries.description: First detected just days ago, 2023 BU will approach within 2,200 miles of our planet’s surface before moving on.

entries.title: Covid Vaccines Targeting Omicron Should Be Standard, Panel Says
entries.description: As advisers to the Food and Drug Administration endorsed ending one era of the Covid vaccination campaign, they also grappled with its future.

entries.title: Your Friday Briefing: China’s Campaign Against ‘Zero-Covid’ Protesters
entries.description: Also, Russian missile attacks in Ukraine and a major deal for Indian women’s cricket.

entries.title: Senior ISIS Leader in Somalia Killed in U.S. Special Operations Raid
entries.description: No civilians or Americans were killed or injured in the operation, officials said.

entries.title: White House Assures Senators That Ukraine Is Committed to Anti-Corruption
entries.description: The firing of several top members of the government in Kyiv had stirred concern over how U.S. aid was being used.

entries.title: Ancient Roman Road’s Beginning Will Remain a Mystery for Now
entries.description: An archaeological dig that began last summer, searching for the long-elusive “first mile” of the Appian Way, has been stymied by ground water.

entries.title: Biden Administration Bans Mining in Boundary Waters Wilderness
entries.description: A 20-year moratorium on new mining activity for more than 225,000 acres of federal land in Minnesota could deal a fatal blow to a proposed Twin Metals copper-nickel mine.

entries.title: As Ukraine awaits promised tanks from the West, the fighting continues.
Hundreds of Children Seeking Asylum in U.K. Are Missing
entries.description: The unaccompanied minors are mostly Albanian teenagers who had been living in hotels. Rights advocates and some lawmakers believe that they have been abducted by criminal gangs.

entries.title: China Arrests ‘Zero Covid’ Protesters in Quiet Crackdown
entries.description: The protests against “zero Covid” were a rare rebuke of Xi Jinping’s rule, and Beijing apparently seeks to deter those who might have been emboldened by them.

entries.title: North Korea Puts Capital in Lockdown to Fight ‘Recurrent Flu’
entries.description: A government notice made no mention of Covid-19, but state media said the authorities were taking measures in the capital to “cope with the daily-worsening world health crisis.”

entries.title: Explosions Heard in Kyiv and Across Ukraine in Latest Strike
entries.description: Kyiv’s mayor ordered people to seek shelter and said that at least one person was dead. There were also reports of missile strikes in western Ukraine and outside Odesa.

entries.title: Israeli Raid on West Bank City Kills Nine Palestinians, Officials Say
entries.description: The deaths, reported by the Palestinian health ministry, bring the toll of Palestinians killed in the Israeli-occupied West Bank so far this year to 29, including at least five children.

entries.title: Video Appears to Show Novak Djokovic’s Father With Pro-Putin Fans at Australian Open
entries.description: In the footage, Srdjan Djokovic seems to pose with fans carrying Russian symbols, which have been banned from the tournament.

entries.title: A Conversation With Nikole Hannah-Jones on the Lasting Impact of the 1619 Project
entries.description: “The 1619 Project” continues to provoke national debate about race and history.

entries.title: As Turkey Elections Loom, Erdogan Fights for Political Future
entries.description: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan is trying to soften the blow of inflation on the population and using legal threats to bolster his position ahead of a vote that could reshape his country.

entries.title: Your Thursday Briefing
entries.description: The effects of Britain’s cost-of-living crisis on families.

entries.title: Ukraine War Accelerates Shift of Power in Europe to the East
entries.description: The war has raised the influence of Central and Eastern European countries with negative views of Russia, amplified calls to expand the E.U. and NATO, and dimmed the power of France and Germany.

entries.title: How Biden Reluctantly Agreed to Send Tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: The decision unlocked a flow of heavy arms from Europe and inched the United States and its NATO allies closer to direct conflict with Russia.

entries.title: Germany and U.S. Pledge to Send Battle Tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: Although welcomed by Kyiv as a critical weapon to expel Russia’s invasion, the Leopard 2 tanks from Germany and Abrams tanks from the United States are unlikely to arrive soon.
